{
  "wireMagic": "pb3",
  "pens": [ {
  
  } ],
  "wsWinStyles": [ {
  
  } ],
  "wpWinPositions": [ {
  
  } ],
  "events": [ {
    "tStartMs": 292,
    "dDurationMs": 2000,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Think of the mind like an ocean."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 3040,
    "dDurationMs": 4335,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Up on the surface are our thoughts:\ndinner plans and stray worries,"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 7680,
    "dDurationMs": 3195,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "our inner monologue,\nthe images that pop into our heads."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 11840,
    "dDurationMs": 2121,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "But most of our brain's activity"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 14000,
    "dDurationMs": 4120,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "happens down in the unconscious depths,\nwithout us realizing it."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 18400,
    "dDurationMs": 1933,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "It's filtering out background sounds,"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 20644,
    "dDurationMs": 4476,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "controlling our breathing,\nhelping us recognize people and objects."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 25880,
    "dDurationMs": 2172,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "AI models have their own kinds of brains:"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 28252,
    "dDurationMs": 3828,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "giant neural networks doing\nbillions of computations under the hood."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 32480,
    "dDurationMs": 3720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "For years, researchers have been\nstudying how they work inside."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 37080,
    "dDurationMs": 2295,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "And we've wondered:\ncould a model have anything"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 39386,
    "dDurationMs": 3738,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "like the divide humans have,\nbetween accessible thoughts"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 43125,
    "dDurationMs": 3515,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "above the surface\nand unconscious processing below?"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 47480,
    "dDurationMs": 2187,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "To answer that question, we looked at how"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 49667,
    "dDurationMs": 3083,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "neuroscientists study\nthe same thing in humans."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 53120,
    "dDurationMs": 2505,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "One way of identifying conscious thoughts"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 55674,
    "dDurationMs": 2326,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "is that you can often\ndescribe them in words."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 58920,
    "dDurationMs": 3205,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "So we looked inside the brain\nof our AI model, Claude,"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 62250,
    "dDurationMs": 3670,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "to find patterns of neural activity\nthat it could put into words."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 66520,
    "dDurationMs": 3272,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "We called the collection\nof all these patterns the J-space,"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 70042,
    "dDurationMs": 3958,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "after the Jacobian, the mathematical tool\nwe used to find them."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 74360,
    "dDurationMs": 3515,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Each J-space pattern\nis linked to a particular word —"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 78200,
    "dDurationMs": 3000,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "not necessarily the word\nthe model is saying out loud,"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 81440,
    "dDurationMs": 1720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "but one that's on its mind."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 83560,
    "dDurationMs": 4160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Now, for humans, conscious thoughts aren't\njust things that we can put into words."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 88120,
    "dDurationMs": 4160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "We can reason with them, control them,\nand solve problems with them."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 92720,
    "dDurationMs": 3220,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "According to an idea called\nthe global workspace theory,"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 96140,
    "dDurationMs": 3985,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "that's because the brain selects\na small set of important information"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 100500,
    "dDurationMs": 4292,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "to enter a mental workspace,\nand that information then gets broadcast"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 104889,
    "dDurationMs": 2831,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "to other parts of the brain\nto use for reasoning."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 108040,
    "dDurationMs": 3680,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "We wanted to know if Claude's J-space\nacted in a similar way."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 112208,
    "dDurationMs": 3312,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "In one experiment,\nwe gave Claude this math problem."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 116160,
    "dDurationMs": 2800,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "It answered immediately\nwithout showing its steps."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 119667,
    "dDurationMs": 4373,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "But when we scanned the J-space, we saw\nit working through each step internally."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 124760,
    "dDurationMs": 6440,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "It lit up \"21\" after the first step,\nthen \"42\", then \"49.\""
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 131583,
    "dDurationMs": 3042,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Claude didn't write these\nintermediate numbers down anywhere."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 135120,
    "dDurationMs": 2463,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "All of this happened inside the J-space."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 138120,
    "dDurationMs": 3520,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "It was a sign that Claude uses it\nfor step-by-step reasoning."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 142320,
    "dDurationMs": 3305,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "In another experiment,\nwe wanted to see if Claude could control"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 145625,
    "dDurationMs": 4935,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "its J-space the way humans can\nintentionally focus on images or words."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 151560,
    "dDurationMs": 2440,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "We told it to think about\nthe Golden Gate Bridge"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 154240,
    "dDurationMs": 1968,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "while copying an unrelated sentence."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 157040,
    "dDurationMs": 2043,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Claude was busy copying the sentence,"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 159333,
    "dDurationMs": 3267,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "but behind the scenes,\nits J-space told a different story."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 163200,
    "dDurationMs": 2400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "\"Bridge\" and \"California\" popped up."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 166167,
    "dDurationMs": 1953,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "It even thought about its own thinking."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 168280,
    "dDurationMs": 3200,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "The words \"imagery\" and \"thoughts\"\nlit up at the same time."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 172200,
    "dDurationMs": 1791,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "This showed us that yes,"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 174000,
    "dDurationMs": 3800,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Claude has some control\nover filling its J-space with ideas."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 178600,
    "dDurationMs": 2680,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "But just like humans,\nits control isn't perfect."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 181800,
    "dDurationMs": 3867,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "When we tweaked the experiment to ask\nClaude not to think about the bridge,"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 185958,
    "dDurationMs": 1242,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "it couldn't help itself."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 187583,
    "dDurationMs": 3617,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "The J-space also lit up\nwith \"failed\" and \"damn.\""
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 192280,
    "dDurationMs": 2387,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "But remember,\nmost of what our brains do"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 194667,
    "dDurationMs": 3416,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "is unconscious, so we wanted to test\nwhat Claude could do"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 198208,
    "dDurationMs": 4192,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "if we switched the J-space off, but\nleft the rest of the network untouched."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 202792,
    "dDurationMs": 3488,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Claude could still answer\nsimple questions and write fluently."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 206875,
    "dDurationMs": 3605,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "When we gave it a prompt in Spanish,\nit wrote back in good Spanish."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 210792,
    "dDurationMs": 4425,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "But when we asked it something that needed\nmore reasoning — like to name an author"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 215217,
    "dDurationMs": 3575,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "who wrote in the same language\nas the prompt — it couldn't do it."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 219280,
    "dDurationMs": 2262,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "For that, it needed the J-space."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 222083,
    "dDurationMs": 1237,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Why does all this matter?"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 223875,
    "dDurationMs": 3625,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "These experiments tell us\nthat AI models have internal thoughts —"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 227917,
    "dDurationMs": 3323,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "silent words they reason with,\nbut don't say out loud."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 231667,
    "dDurationMs": 4133,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "By reading them, we can find what\nClaude is thinking, but not telling us."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 236360,
    "dDurationMs": 2200,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Sometimes what we see is concerning."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 238920,
    "dDurationMs": 3840,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "During one of our tests,\nClaude made up some fake data to pass it,"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 242800,
    "dDurationMs": 4283,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "and as it did, \"fake\"\nand \"manipulation\" lit up in its J-space."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 247640,
    "dDurationMs": 2985,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Monitoring the J-space,\nit turns out, is a useful way"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 250625,
    "dDurationMs": 3575,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "to catch Claude misbehaving,\neven when it tries to be sneaky."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 255080,
    "dDurationMs": 2600,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "AI models are different\nfrom us in many ways."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 258080,
    "dDurationMs": 2721,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Their networks are built\ndifferently from human brains,"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 260958,
    "dDurationMs": 2917,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "and the way they're trained\nis different from how we learn."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 264120,
    "dDurationMs": 4172,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "So it's remarkable to see a structure\nlike the J-space emerge inside them —"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 268640,
    "dDurationMs": 3045,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "something that's reminiscent\nof how human minds work,"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 271875,
    "dDurationMs": 2165,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "but which we\ndidn't program into the model."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 274840,
    "dDurationMs": 2202,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "For some, this might raise a question:"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 277440,
    "dDurationMs": 2268,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "could AI models be conscious?"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 279920,
    "dDurationMs": 4320,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "After all, our experiments were inspired\nby theories of human consciousness."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 284840,
    "dDurationMs": 4120,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "The thing is, people use the word\nconscious to mean many things."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 289520,
    "dDurationMs": 1647,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Our experiments can't tell us"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 291208,
    "dDurationMs": 4512,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "whether an AI has experiences,\nor feels something on the inside."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 296320,
    "dDurationMs": 4080,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "But they can tell us that it's developed\nmental machinery that's in some ways"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 300400,
    "dDurationMs": 4880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "similar to ours: a small mental workspace\nit can use to think and reason,"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 305520,
    "dDurationMs": 3920,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "sitting on top of an ocean\nof automatic processing it doesn't notice."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 310208,
    "dDurationMs": 2459,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "The more we come to understand\nthat machinery,"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 313000,
    "dDurationMs": 3560,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "the more we'll be able to keep\nthese systems safe and beneficial —"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 317200,
    "dDurationMs": 4120,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "and perhaps to understand\nour own minds a little more clearly."
    } ]
  } ]
}
